CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 24, 1953, pg. 30, reads: "Celebration of YMCA Week Starts This Saturday - Too-Shay Not! Believe it or not, some of the youth at the Centre Avenue branch go in for the ancient sport of fencing. And why not? Fencing required great skill, develops co-ordination, alertness. It's good for the girls even though their dueling may not go any further than some deadly repartee. The instructor is Leonard Stadd. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Young men and women, possibly including instructor Leonard Stadd, fencing in Centre Avenue YMCA
